                    n="panathenaia">
                    <head>Panathenaia</head>
                    <p>The Panathenaia held at Athens was two-fold, one festival being held annually, and the other celebrated every five years, the latter called the Great Panathenaia. Isocrates says in his Panathenaikos: <q>"shortly before the Panathenaia"</q>. Erichthonius, son of Hephaistos, was the first to conduct the festival, according to the reports of Hellanikos and Adrotion, <pb n="p.235"/>each in the first books of their Atthis respectively. Before Erichthonius' time the festival was simply called the Athenaia, as Istros makes clear in the third book of his Attika.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
